      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "MINIMALDATA is not a consensus rule, and transactions that use non-minimal pushes or non-minimally encoded numbers are perfectly valid in blocks. I don't think we should fail to decode them. I don't really have good advice here, as I'm fine with somehow marking these as different, but they shouldn't fail to decode.\n",
